description:
To cope with our expansion, we are looking for an energetic person with PRC experience to join our Company.  You will report directly to the Company Secretary and be responsible for the following duties:

Responsibilities:

Assist in handling company secretarial duties for the group of companies;
Assist in contract drafting and review, contract management and other legal matters;
Assist in handling insurance matters;
Assist in ad-hoc projects and tasks as assigned.

Qualifications:

Degree or above in Corporate Governance or related discipline, member of HKICS / ICSA;
At least 5 years' relevant experiences gained in large-scale corporations or professional firms, candidates with more experience may be considered for a senior role;
Sound experience in preparing corporate secretarial and legal documents for PRC will be an advantage;
Good command of the English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Proficient in Microsoft Office (i.e. MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint);
Self-motivated, independent, requires minimal supervision, diligent and resourceful;
Immediate availability is preferred.
Working Location: Sham Tseng (Free Shuttle Bus Service running along different locations in Yuen Long, Tuen Mun, Tsuen Wan and Shamshuipo to / from office are provided)

Responsibilities:

Perform company secretarial duties for the Group, listed company and its subsidiaries;
Draft and prepare annual / interim reports, announcements and circulars;
Organize meetings for the board, committees and shareholders, and prepare relevant board papers and minutes;
Maintain and update statutory records / filings in compliance with HK Listing Rules;
Assist to review on all legal and compliance documents including internal, external contracts and agreements;
Perform any ad hoc projects and tasks assigned from management.
Requirements:

Degree holder, preferably with associate / graduate of HKICS / ICSA or equivalent;
Minimum of 4 years or above relevant experience in listed companies is required;
Prior hands-on working experience in handling company secretarial matters is a MUST;
Knowledge in Companies Ordinance and Listing Rules;
Excellent command of English and Chinese;
Well-organized, self-motivated and able to work independently;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Assistant Manager.
We Offer:
Competitive remuneration package
5 Days Work & Bank Holidays
Attendance Bonus
Meal Allowance
Discretionary Bonus
Medical Insurance
We provide attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits for the right candidate. Interested parties please send detailed resume with current and expected salaries to Human Resources Department by clicking "Apply Now" or fax to: 2530 2218.
All information collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, only shortlisted candidates will be notified.

Welcome to visit our website: http://www.bsgroup.com.hk/ for more information.

Responsibilities

Reporting to the General Manager of the Company Secretarial Department, the successful candidate will be responsible for performing a full range of company secretarial duties and services as well as statutory compliance for listed and private companies. He/she will assist to advise on the Company’s major decisions, build and maintain regulations and legal compliance framework, draft and review announcement, provide training to staff and coordinate with other departments on compliance issues of the Company. He/she will also undertake special projects as assigned by the Company from time to time.

Requirements

-          Recognized university degree in relevant discipline, holder of law degree advantage;

-          Member of The Chartered Governance Institute;

-          Minimum 10 years’ relevant company secretarial experience, of which at least 5 years at managerial level in Hong Kong listed companies;

-          Well-versed in Hong Kong Listing Rules, Companies Ordinance, Securities and Futures Ordinance and relevant rules and regulations;

-          Strong business acumen, good analytical, interpersonal, communication and managerial skills;

-          Mature, meticulous, well organized and able to work under pressure with strong sense of responsibility;

-          Well organized, independent and able to work under pressure; and

-          Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (Cantonese and Putonghua).

 Attractive and competitive remuneration package will be offered to the right candidate. Candidates with less experience will be considered as Deputy Secretarial Manager or Secretarial Officer.

Application with full resume, current and expected salary, and date of availability should be sent through email. For details of the Company, please visit our website: www.gdi.com.hk.

Information provided will be for recruitment purpose within the GDI group and only short-listed candidates will be contacted. We comply with all applicable laws and regulations of HKSAR in handling applications.

Job Responsibilities: 

Prepare announcement, annual and interim reports; 
Responsible for company secretarial duties of subsidiaries;  
Assist in drafting transactions and company secretarial tasks of listed company; 
Coordinate and organize shareholder and board meeting;  
Provide investor relations (IR) support on presentation materials and event coordination;
Handle any ad-hoc assignments.

Job Requirements: 

Degree holder with minimum 3 years’ experience in Company Secretarial disciplines;
Chartered Company Secretary and familiar with Hong Kong Listing Rule is highly preferred;  
Experience in Chinese based companies/ property developer/ listed company is an advantage;
Excellent command in both written and spoken English and Mandarin;
Willing to learn and with “Can do” attitude;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Assistant Manager, IR & Company Secretary

We offer attractive remuneration package and excellent career development to the right candidate. Interested parties please clicking "Apply Now" to submit full resume with availability, current and expected salary to us.

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. All information provided by applicants will be treated in strictest confidence and handled confidentially for recruitment-related purposes within the company and our associated company. Applicants may be considered for other suitable positions within the company over a one-year period, after which their personal data will be destroyed.

